.TH "netlink_set_err" 9 "netlink_set_err" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
netlink_set_err \- report error to broadcast listeners
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" netlink_set_err
.BI "(struct sock *ssk "  ","
.BI "u32 portid "  ","
.BI "u32 group "  ","
.BI "int code "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ssk" 12
the kernel netlink socket, as returned by \fBnetlink_kernel_create\fP
.IP "portid" 12
the PORTID of a process that we want to skip (if any)
.IP "group" 12
the broadcast group that will notice the error
.IP "code" 12
error code, must be negative (as usual in kernelspace)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function returns the number of broadcast listeners that have set the
NETLINK_NO_ENOBUFS socket option.
